<p><b>I just found the way to remove purple screen after login-ing Ubuntu 20.04.</b></p>
<ul>
  <li><span style="color:red"><b>WARNING!!</b></span> I am very very newbie, so my solution may be wrong.</li>
  <li>Before trying this, I recommend you to find another solution. Maybe there is some better one!</li>
  <li><span style="color:purple"> <b>Summary</b></span>: Find the <b><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libgnome-shell.so</code></b> file, and change the color code <b><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">#4f194c</code>.</b></li>
</ul>

<p><br /></p>

<h2><b>ë°©ë²•</b></h2>
